      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I understand correctly, the interceptor will be called for every RPC call. Will it be more efficient if all services write data to a fixed test specific directory, with service name as subdirectory, and retrieve the whole directory before test complete?",
      "revId": "0e64f732710da00ae6e3dc046591abcd17201cf7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c0e1ae45_73aedc90",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/internal/rpc/client.go",
